Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.widgets

Class ClientDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.tabris.widgets.ClientDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class ClientDialog
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    A ClientDialog is a client side dialog. A client uses native dialogs to visualize the ClientDialog. For this reason dialogs may vary form client to client.

    Since:
    1.4

      • setButton

        public ClientDialog setButton​(ClientDialog.ButtonType type,
                              java.lang.String text)

        Sets a ClientDialog button with the specified ClientDialog.ButtonType. The client is responsible to position the button on its right place.

        Parameters:
        type - the ClientDialog.ButtonType of the button. Must not be null.
        text - the text of the button. Must not be null or empty.

      • setButton

        public ClientDialog setButton​(ClientDialog.ButtonType type,
                              java.lang.String text,
                              org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Listener listener)

        Sets a ClientDialog button with the specified ClientDialog.ButtonType. The client is responsible to position the button on its right place. When the button was pressed the Listener will be notified.

        Parameters:
        type - the ClientDialog.ButtonType of the button. Must not be null.
        text - the text of the button. Must not be null or empty.
        listener - the listener to notify when the button was pressed. May be null.
